<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="183" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1022,1301]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">
While 
<bibRefCitation author="Saint-Hilaire, A." box="[209,433,1022,1048]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183" pagination="289 - 295" refId="ref8353" refString="Saint-Hilaire, A. (1828) LXVI Luhea Willd. Flora Brasiliae meridionalis 1 (8): 289 - 295." type="journal article" year="1828">Saint-Hilaire (1828)</bibRefCitation>
did not mention a particular specimen to describe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saint-Hilaire" authorityYear="1828" box="[981,1104,1022,1048]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="3" pageNumber="183" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="laxiflora">
<emphasis box="[981,1104,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">L. laxiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, three of his original specimens are in 
<collectorName box="[211,356,1058,1085]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">Herbarium P</collectorName>
, where his collection is kept (
<bibRefCitation author="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S." box="[703,972,1058,1084]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183" refId="ref8497" refString="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S. (1976 - 1988) Taxonomic Literature: A selective guide to botanical publications and collections with dates, commentaries and types, 2 nd ed., Smithsonian Libraries, last updated 28 Jun. 2012. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 48631" type="book" year="1976">Stafleu &amp; Cowan 1976</bibRefCitation>
–1988: 1064). 
<bibRefCitation author="Cunha, M. C. S." box="[1139,1296,1058,1085]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183" pagination="5 - 41" refId="ref7419" refString="Cunha, M. C. S. (1985) Revisao das especies do genero Luehea Willd. (Tiliaceae), ocorrentes no estado do Rio de Janeiro. Sellowia, Anais Botanicos do Herbario Barbosa Rodrigues 37: 5 - 41." type="journal article" year="1985">
<collectingCountry box="[1139,1212,1058,1084]" name="Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">Cunha</collectingCountry>
(1985)
</bibRefCitation>
indicated the ‘holotype’ in P, but without having seen it and specifying an identification number. Consequently, the status of the type needs to be corrected as 
<typeStatus box="[472,575,1130,1156]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">lectotype</typeStatus>
and it can be considered as a first-step typification (Art. 9.17 of the ICN). In accordance with Arts. 9.3 and 9.4 of the ICN, we designate herein specimen P 
<date box="[1016,1128,1166,1192]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183" value="2938-02-14">
<collectingDate box="[1016,1128,1166,1192]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183" value="2938-02-14">02142938</collectingDate>
</date>
as the second-step 
<typeStatus box="[1349,1452,1166,1192]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">lectotype</typeStatus>
by choosing the best preserved specimen congruent with the protologue’s description. Based on the type materials and the original descriptions, the application of the name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Saint-Hilaire" authorityYear="1828" box="[725,849,1238,1264]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="3" pageNumber="183" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="laxiflora">
<emphasis box="[725,849,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">L. laxiflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is confirmed as a heterotypic synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Willdenow" authorityYear="1801" box="[1319,1444,1239,1264]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Luehea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="3" pageNumber="183" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="speciosa">
<emphasis box="[1319,1444,1239,1264]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="183">L. speciosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as previously accepted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Schumann, K." box="[432,634,1274,1301]" pageId="3" pageNumber="183" pagination="117 - 200" refId="ref8376" refString="Schumann, K. (1886) Tilliaceae. Flora Brasiliensis, enumeratio plantarum in Brasilia hactenus detectarum: quas suis aliorumque botanicorum studiis descriptas et methodo naturali digestas partim icone illustratas 12 (3): 117 - 200. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 454" type="journal article" year="1886">Schumann (1886)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
